  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;abjuration;\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;adept 3, alchemist 3, bard 3, cleric/oracle 3, inquisitor 3, medium 3, mesmerist 3, paladin 3, shaman 3, sorcerer/wizard 4, spiritualist 3, witch 3;\n    <strong>Domain</strong>&nbsp;Liberation 3;\n    \n    \n    <strong>Bloodline</strong>&nbsp;Celestial 4;\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;creature or object touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;instantaneous<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates (harmless);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p><i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> can remove all <i>curse</i>s on an object or a creature. If the target is a creature, you must make a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) against the DC of each <i>curse</i> affecting the target.</p><p>Success means that the <i>curse</i> is removed. <i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> does not remove the <i>curse</i> from a <i>curse</i>d shield, weapon, or suit of armor, although a successful caster level check enables the creature afflicted with any such <i>curse</i>d item to remove and get rid of it.</p><p><i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> counters and dispels bestow <i>curse</i>.</p>\n</div>\n",
